3. SYBIL RESISTANCE

Current issue:
A malicious actor can generate many Ed25519 identities and appear as many peers.

Using libp2p identities guarantees uniqueness of one keypair but does not prevent cheap multiple identities.

Need at least one of:
- proof-of-work / costly identity generation
- rate-limited identity registration
- identity age weighting
- resource testing
- peer diversity constraints per bucket / subnet / prefix


